comments.body:
@DarwinJS I think it entirely depends on the using context. Can you assess how PowerShell uses environment variables? As a result, we could open a few sub-Issues to fix the specific problems.

But it seems first we need to conclude - Environment variables vs CoreFX special folder API.
/cc @SteveL-MSFT

@DarwinJS Feel free share any ideas! Later we can always open a new discussion for a more specific case.

From the link:
>The twelve-factor app stores config in environment variables (often shortened to env vars or env). Env vars are easy to change between deploys without changing any code; unlike config files, there is little chance of them being checked into the code repo accidentally; and unlike custom config files, or other config mechanisms such as Java System Properties, they are a language- and OS-agnostic standard.
